wikipedia_page.main: Henry Norman (12 December 1801 – 28 December 1867) was an English cricketer with amateur status. He was associated with Kent and Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC) and made his first-class debut in 1827. He played for the Gentlemen against the Players.

response: * Sir Henry Norman, 1st Baronet (1858–1939), English journalist and Liberal politician
